  1. Set a local CI pipeline put Unit tests, integration tests and some longer running tests in there.  Shedule runs.  Trigger runs.  Can we have pause button ... in case live development want priority.
  2. Buy a new PC with 12-16 cores, 64GB ram, 2T SSD drive.  Use the new rig for live development run SI server on the old rig ... until it goes up in a puff of smoke :)
- Try remove maybe of Types.C files in the libraries other than qcCommon.
## Solids / plane waves

- **APW energy-dependent overlap** (`APW_IBS` is an `IrrepBasisSet<dcmplx>` but deliberately not an
  `Orbital_1E_IBS`): solve the nonlinear secular eq by iterating ŌĆö guess EŌéĆ, build H(EŌéĆ),O(EŌéĆ); solve the
  generalized problem ŌåÆ ╬Ą_n(EŌéĆ); set EŌéĆŌåÉEŌéü until fixed point. Like an SCF except we find E* (not a density)
  and S(E) also changes each iteration.
  Need to see wat real SCF looks like on APW with DFT. 
- **Mid-level plan:** (1) go far along lineage A & B; (2) lineage A: `template<isM_1E_Evaluator E> class
  EPlaneWave_IBS<E>`, migrate the hardcoded PW IBSs one at a time (most data ŌåÆ evaluators); (3) graft onto
  lineage B; (4) e-e repulsion (needs the DFT upgrade first). Also: GPW/GAPW after FLAPW ŌĆö we have Gaussian
  integral engines in `src/BasisSet/Molecule` if that helps.

- Submodule tiny-diffs (blaze, wignerSymbols, libxc): CMake min-version noise + blaze compiler warnings.
  libxc xc.h mtime churn is patched (write-only-if-changed). Better long-term handling? (keep a patch,
  re-apply after checkout?)


# By library or project-module

## qcHamiltonian

- **bare->r\* rename** (remove transitional aliases): bare names (`Static_HT`, `Dynamic_HT`,
  `Hamiltonian`, `Static_CC`, `Dynamic_CC`, `DM_CD`, `Composite_CD`, `obs_t`, ...) are still
  `using X = rX` shims so ~200 existing sites didn't churn. Do the codebase-wide rename. NOTE the
  `rHamiltonian` rename must also dissolve the `qchem::Hamiltonian` namespace-vs-type shadow
  (the `::Hamiltonian` / `qchem::Hamiltonian::` qualifications scattered around are working around it).
- **newCD double-duty redesign**: `Dynamic_HT_Imp` caches by Irrep and `newCD(cd)` does two jobs
  (cache-clear + refit-trigger). The cache-freshness bug was fixed (commit 582f1d05: GetMatrix clears
  on cd-change), but the deeper smell remains ŌĆö split the two responsibilities. See
  [[project_hamiltonian_dynamic_cache_bug]].

### Friendly libxc interface
- Clients shouldn't have to look up a function id. Pick a few popular/common functionals we want, make enums,
  handle params for the user ŌĆö hide that libxc is under the hood.

