## qcAtom_BS
- **Dirac/RKB:** 1s orbital not properly normalized; track kinetic factors (0.5, c, 2c).
- **Dirac/RKB:** `Orbital_DHF_IBS.C::merge_xxx`: use `blazem::submatrix`.
- **Atom evaluators:** Gaussian integrals via recursion `Fact[n]/pow(2,n)` (consider `constexpr`); convert
  the BSpline Fortran GL integrator (`Atom/Evaluators/BSpline/Internal/gauleg.f`) to C++/blaze and fold into
  qcMesh ŌĆö BSpline and PW should share one 1-D GL.
- `op()(rvec3_t)` is the universal evaluation interface (full angular dependence, real Ylm ŌĆö the future GUI
  needs honest truth). Atom DFT integration should exploit spherical symmetry analytically (1-D radial ├Ś 4ŽĆ),
  NOT fake a 3-D grid down one axis. Make integration a polymorphic quadrature strategy chosen by the basis's
  symmetry (atom carries YFactory). **Principle to lock now:** `op(rvec3_t)` is always honest; a fast
  `op(double r)` may exist only as the radial integrator's internal fast-path, never a public alternative.
  Defer to GUI time, but don't let the deferral accrete a flag.
- Fix BSpline::EvaluatorCommon<K>::RadialType() too long, other just do Name()
