## qcStructure

## qcSymmetry

- **Space-group support** ŌĆö extend qcSymmetry from molecular point groups + Bloch k-labels to crystal space
  groups. Three sub-tasks: (1) **detect** the ops from cell+basis (spglib-style); (2) **represent** `{R|Žä}`
  and apply them (to k in reciprocal space; to positions/density in real space); (3) **BZ machinery** ŌĆö star
  of k, irreducible wedge, integration weights.
  - **Tier A** ŌĆö point group acting on k (+ time-reversal `kŌåÆŌłÆk`). Enough for BZ reduction (consumes only the
    point-group part; symmorphic-friendly). This is the provider for the qcLattice_3D *BZ-symmetry reduction*
    item.
  - **Tier B** ŌĆö full space group with fractional translations Žä ŌåÆ non-symmorphic `e^{ŌłÆiG┬ĘŽä}` phases,
    density/Hamiltonian symmetrization, crystal SALCs (solid analogue of the molecular SALC work).
  - Reuses the molecular point-group core: a space group Ōēł point group Ōŗē lattice translations.

